00:59:04,030 --> 00:59:06,100
My wife was really shocked that day.

557
00:59:06,800 --> 00:59:08,870
So she wrote some stuff on the online notice board...

558
00:59:11,610 --> 00:59:13,480
of the hospital website out of anger.

559
00:59:14,480 --> 00:59:16,850
Please let me apologize on her behalf.

560
00:59:19,050 --> 00:59:23,050
This is a small town, and your reputation matters.

561
00:59:23,390 --> 00:59:24,650
What she did...

562
00:59:25,620 --> 00:59:27,560
was very disrespectful to you.

563
00:59:29,160 --> 00:59:30,230
And I know...

564
00:59:32,260 --> 00:59:35,830
that it will only remain as a civil case.

565
00:59:38,230 --> 00:59:40,640
But can you please not sue Da Kyung for having destroyed your marriage?

566
00:59:44,910 --> 00:59:45,940
What...

567
00:59:46,840 --> 00:59:48,210
do you need me to do?

568
00:59:51,550 --> 00:59:53,320
Are you proposing a deal?

569
00:59:57,720 --> 01:00:00,620
My goodness, look at her. She's so brazen.

570
01:00:01,060 --> 01:00:02,160
She's unbelievable.

571
01:00:02,160 --> 01:00:05,060
I know. I can't believe she still lives here.

572
01:00:06,860 --> 01:00:08,400
She's ruining the reputation of our neighborhood.

573
01:00:08,560 --> 01:00:11,000
She's shopping for groceries after having destroyed a family?

574
01:00:11,000 --> 01:00:12,570
She's got some nerve.

575
01:00:13,940 --> 01:00:15,100
My gosh.

576
01:00:23,450 --> 01:00:25,780
Will you look at her? What is she even doing here?

577
01:00:26,920 --> 01:00:28,220
This card was declined.

578
01:00:31,150 --> 01:00:33,820
That can't be. Please try again.

579
01:00:35,890 --> 01:00:37,030
(Swipe card)

580
01:00:37,030 --> 01:00:38,190
(Transaction denied. Please try again.)

581
01:00:39,330 --> 01:00:40,560
It was rejected.

582
01:00:44,070 --> 01:00:46,200
How can you suddenly freeze my credit cards?

583
01:00:46,670 --> 01:00:48,040
You said to stay out of it.

584
01:00:49,140 --> 01:00:50,770
Doesn't that jerk give you money for expenses?

585
01:00:51,240 --> 01:00:53,140
Must you go this far?

586
01:01:02,820 --> 01:01:03,890
Daddy.

587
01:01:04,850 --> 01:01:07,620
Can't you help Tae Oh? He's talented.

588
01:01:08,290 --> 01:01:10,190
He'll succeed if you support him.

589
01:01:10,190 --> 01:01:13,400
Is that why he bled his wife dry all these years?

590
01:01:13,630 --> 01:01:17,200
Da Kyung. Why are you such a poor judge of people?

591
01:01:18,130 --> 01:01:19,330
Shut it and get out.

592
01:01:20,440 --> 01:01:21,940
I'll pretend I don't have a daughter.

593
01:01:29,080 --> 01:01:30,180
Daddy.

594
01:01:34,180 --> 01:01:35,580
Please.

595
01:01:37,550 --> 01:01:38,650
Please, Daddy.

596
01:01:42,090 --> 01:01:43,190
Da Kyung.

597
01:01:47,460 --> 01:01:49,060
It's not too late.

598
01:01:49,300 --> 01:01:50,500
Break up with him.

599
01:01:51,270 --> 01:01:55,000
If you do, Daddy will take care of you...

600
01:01:55,700 --> 01:01:57,340
and the baby.

601
01:01:57,970 --> 01:01:59,980
Listen to me.

602
01:02:01,640 --> 01:02:02,710
Okay?

603
01:02:04,150 --> 01:02:05,810
I love him.

604
01:02:08,680 --> 01:02:10,050
I can't leave him.

605
01:02:14,660 --> 01:02:16,660
He hit his wife in front of his child...

606
01:02:16,660 --> 01:02:18,690
and was arrested for assault.

607
01:02:19,760 --> 01:02:20,930
But what? Love?

608
01:02:21,430 --> 01:02:23,930
- Have you lost your mind? - It's not like that!

609
01:02:27,240 --> 01:02:29,600
That woman set him up.

610
01:02:32,140 --> 01:02:33,310
Daddy.

611
01:02:39,350 --> 01:02:40,480
Fine.

612
01:02:43,750 --> 01:02:45,190
Pretend you don't have a daughter anymore.

613
01:02:48,290 --> 01:02:49,420
I won't come back.

614
01:03:27,330 --> 01:03:28,460
I reported...

615
01:03:29,700 --> 01:03:31,300
In Kyu for assault.

616
01:03:32,200 --> 01:03:35,500
The lawyer says he won't get out easily because he has...

617
01:03:36,500 --> 01:03:38,010
several priors.

618
01:03:39,210 --> 01:03:40,380
That's good.

619
01:03:42,910 --> 01:03:44,550
It's thanks to you.

620
01:03:45,050 --> 01:03:46,410
I didn't do anything.

621
01:03:48,080 --> 01:03:49,380
It was all you.

622
01:03:50,050 --> 01:03:51,920
You showed me by example...

623
01:03:53,960 --> 01:03:55,520
how to get out of it.

624
01:04:00,300 --> 01:04:02,430
I used your situation.

625
01:04:04,200 --> 01:04:06,670
I'm the one who said to use it as much as you wanted.

626
01:04:07,940 --> 01:04:09,000
Why did you do it?

627
01:04:11,340 --> 01:04:12,540
What about you?

628
01:04:17,010 --> 01:04:19,480
You were the first person to help me...

629
01:04:22,720 --> 01:04:24,590
when I was being hit.

630
01:04:27,760 --> 01:04:30,530
Why did you get so involved and go so far...

631
01:04:34,700 --> 01:04:35,900
to save me?

632
01:05:03,990 --> 01:05:05,260
Did you go out?

633
01:05:07,160 --> 01:05:10,630
I think the hospital director made a big miscalculation.

634
01:05:11,700 --> 01:05:15,640
Psychiatry is going to be a big minus in our profits.

635
01:05:17,510 --> 01:05:21,440
Should I go out and market myself if I want to stay on?

636
01:05:30,990 --> 01:05:34,090
Divorce is like a war, right?

637
01:05:34,660 --> 01:05:35,990
There's no winner or loser.

638
01:05:39,690 --> 01:05:40,960
I know from experience.

639
01:05:49,940 --> 01:05:51,540
Albeit it was unconventional,

640
01:05:53,340 --> 01:05:56,180
I found out the source of your trauma,

641
01:05:56,710 --> 01:05:58,780
so why don't you try receiving treatment for it?

642
01:05:58,950 --> 01:06:01,320
I'm pretty well-respected in Seoul.

643
01:06:02,780 --> 01:06:03,990
I'm fine.

644
01:06:05,250 --> 01:06:07,360
Do you have experience treating alcoholics?

645
01:06:07,960 --> 01:06:09,660
I would like to make a referral.

646
01:06:10,230 --> 01:06:11,330
Who?

647
01:06:14,200 --> 01:06:17,830
(Doctor Ji Sun Woo)

648
01:06:20,640 --> 01:06:22,100
How's your injury?

649
01:06:22,570 --> 01:06:24,940
- Are you okay? - I'm okay.

650
01:06:25,710 --> 01:06:26,840
It's all better.

651
01:06:33,150 --> 01:06:34,920
Joon Young was shocked too, wasn't he?

652
01:06:35,650 --> 01:06:37,120
That psycho jerk.

653
01:06:37,490 --> 01:06:39,620
How dare he beat you up?

654
01:06:41,060 --> 01:06:42,190
Good job.

655
01:06:42,920 --> 01:06:46,460
You can live with a cheater, but not with someone who's violent.

656
01:06:48,860 --> 01:06:50,100
Sorry about everything.

657
01:06:51,030 --> 01:06:53,070
I took our my annoyance at you.

658
01:06:53,070 --> 01:06:55,470
Don't be. I'm the one who's sorry.

659
01:06:57,010 --> 01:07:00,310
I really wronged you in so many ways, Sun Woo.

660
01:07:03,280 --> 01:07:05,280
Hey, have you heard?

661
01:07:06,110 --> 01:07:07,480
Tae Oh is leaving Gosan.

662
01:07:09,220 --> 01:07:11,750
The rumors have spread everywhere in this tiny city.

663
01:07:11,750 --> 01:07:13,350
How could he stick around?

664
01:07:14,160 --> 01:07:17,290
He must have some shame. He's moving somewhere no one knows him.

665
01:07:18,790 --> 01:07:21,500
Anyway, congrats on your new start.

666
01:07:22,000 --> 01:07:23,300
I wish you only happiness going forward.

667
01:07:26,230 --> 01:07:29,100
You should date if you find a nice guy...

668
01:07:29,840 --> 01:07:30,940
and show that jerk.

669
01:07:31,710 --> 01:07:33,210
Don't jinx me.

670
01:07:33,510 --> 01:07:34,810
I'm sick of men.

671
01:07:35,840 --> 01:07:36,980
See you.

672
01:09:13,410 --> 01:09:14,510
Joon Young?

673
01:09:15,880 --> 01:09:17,310
I'm home.

674
01:09:27,460 --> 01:09:28,660
What did it mean...

675
01:09:30,060 --> 01:09:31,290
to be married?

676
01:09:37,870 --> 01:09:39,900
What did the times we shared mean?

677
01:09:43,940 --> 01:09:48,110
What was the point of attacking each other so cruelly?

678
01:11:11,160 --> 01:11:12,330
Because we loved...

679
01:11:14,030 --> 01:11:15,160
Because we hated each other...

680
01:11:17,930 --> 01:11:18,970
In the end,

681
01:11:20,370 --> 01:11:21,670
because we're all human...

682
01:11:24,410 --> 01:11:27,010
So many questions floated around in my head.

683
01:11:36,650 --> 01:11:37,720
But,

684
01:11:40,590 --> 01:11:42,360
I decided not to ask questions anymore.

